1. What Information Do We Collect?
We, our service providers, and other third parties acting on our behalf collect a variety of types of personal information. This may include when you use our Site and Apps, register or create an online account with us, and use our services. The information we collect may include the following information:
•
Contact Information
, such as your name, email address, mailing address, zip code, postal code, phone number, and location-based information (including city and state derived from your IP address);
•
Information for purposes of verification
,
such as
passport information, driver’s license information, permanent and temporary addresses, and tax-related information;
•
Account Information
, such as your email address, password and birthday;
•
Device and browsing information
, including IP address,GPS coordinates, referral website, browser and device type, operating system version, webpage navigation, information about how often you use our Site andApps, the events that occur within the Site and Apps, aggregated usage, performance data, where the application was downloaded from, and other information about your activities on our Site, other websites, and our Apps(collectively, "automatically collected information");
•
Device phonebook information
, meaning your contacts and related information you store on your device, so long as you’ve explicitly granted this permission to us within our Apps (note that you may revoke this permission at any time within the Vivid Picks app);
• Commercial information
relating to records of contests you enter, including information about contest entry fees you have paid, prize history, and/or deposit and withdrawal information.
•
Purchase information
relating to tickets bought through ourApps, including billing address, credit card or other payment information, links, PayPal address, name and address of a gift recipient, and name and phone number of a third person who will pick up items for you;
•
Your photograph
, only if you agree to provide it and then upload it, may be collected for the purpose of verifying your identity when creating an account with us or buying tickets on our Apps or for use as your in-App profile picture or avatar.
•
Publicly available information and purchased information
, including information about you from publicly available databases (such as demographic information, media consumption, previous purchases, shopping habits, loyalty program information, lifestyle preferences or information to validate or update the information we collect from or about you) and information purchased from your cell phone company and your email domain. This information is collected for the purposes of anti-fraud verification and marketing;
•
Information you provide through social media
, including information that you use in connection with our Site and Apps, or that share or allow you to share information with us, such as Facebook. For example, if you use functionalities, plugins, widgets, or tools from social media platforms or networks in connection with our Site and Apps (for example, if you choose to log in, access or otherwise connect to our Apps through Facebook),we will collect the information that you share with us, or that those social media platforms or networks share with us; and
•
Other information or content
that you provide through ourApps. Any information you provide in our Apps, such as by uploading a new avatar picture or reacting to other users’ picks, may be read, collected, and used by others who access them.
2. How Do We Collect Information?
We collect personal information through our Site and Apps, and through email and other communications and interactions with you. We also obtain information about you from third parties, as described below:
A. Information You Provide
• Information you share when you use the Site and Apps
, such as when you visit us online, enter fantasy sports contests, purchase tickets, create an account with us, participate in anti-fraud verification, subscribe to our email newsletter, post information or content within our Apps, contact us for customer support or otherwise communicate with us, enter contests or sweepstakes, participate in surveys, register for other activities on our Site and Apps, or grant us permission to access, import, sync, and/or copy your device phonebook information (i.e., your contact list);
• Information automatically collected
, including information that we, our affiliates and/or third parties we work with collect from the computer, tablet, phone, or other device that you use to access our Site or Apps, or that you use to open an email from us. This information may be collected through first-party and third-party cookies, pixel tags, web beacons, SDKs,  scripts, and/or similar technologies on ourSite, Apps and emails, or through mobile analytics software that allows us to better understand the functionality of our Apps on your phone. This collection includes automatically collected information, and generally does not include personal information that directly identifies you unless another user authorizes us to import your contact information, you provide it through ourSite or Apps, or you choose to share it with us.
B. Information from Other Sources
We may acquire information from other sources as follows:
• From other trusted third-party sources
, to update or supplement the information that you provide or that we collect automatically. This includes, for example, information from service providers that we use, publicly available databases or third parties from whom we have purchased data such as public databases or data aggregators, and information purchased from your cell phone company and your email domain. You authorize your wireless carrier to use or disclose information about your account and your wireless device, if available, to us or our service providers for the duration of your business relationship, solely to help them identify you or your wireless device and to prevent fraud. See Section 3 below for how we treat your data.
• From our partners and service providers
including, for example, business partners, analytics vendors, marketing partners, advertising networks, search information providers and service providers. We may use this information to help us maintain the accuracy of the information we collect, verify your identity, perform fraud prevention activities, personalize your experience with our services, target our communications so that we can inform you of products, services or other offers that may be of interest to you, to measure quality and responses, and for internal business analysis or other business purposes, including those described below in Section 3.
• Information provided about you by other users of our Site or Apps
(for example, when another user purchases tickets for you as a gift, when another user designates you to pick up tickets on his or her behalf, or when another user authorizes us to import your contact information).
We may combine the information we receive from and about you, including information you provide to us and information collected automatically through our Site and Apps, as well as information collected offline, across other computers or devices that you may use, and from third party sources.
3. How Do We Use Information?
We use the personal information that we collect and obtain to conduct our business and to provide you with the products, services, games, contests, and experiences that you request or that we think may be of interest to you. We use information:
• To provide you with services
, including to administer, improve and secure the Site and Apps, process deposits and withdrawals, provide you with accurate ticket listings, fulfill your ticket orders and process your payments, calculate ticket shipping options, verify your identity and protect the integrity of Vivid Picks contests and the ticket marketplace, conduct anti-fraud verification, process, create, maintain and service your account, send you relevant newsletters, offers, and promotions, and provide you with products and services that you request or that we think may be of interest to you, including providing you with reward credits through the Vivid Seats
Rewards Program
for ticket purchases you make via our Apps, and for the purpose of generating, processing, and otherwise managing a transaction initiated by you in our Apps. We may use your IP address and GPS coordinates to infer your city and state location in order to ensure you are located in jurisdiction that permits operation of our real-money gaming Services and/or to recommend nearby events that may be of interest to you. This could include sending you emails, push notifications or alerts regarding such nearby events;
• To contact you
and deliver information to you that, in some cases, is targeted to your interests. These communications may contain links for preference management and, where appropriate, unsubscribe links should you decide you do not want to receive further communications;
• To respond to you
, when you place an order, correspond with us by email or otherwise communicate with us for customer service purposes, make a request or inquiry, enter a contest or sweepstakes, complete a survey or share a comment or concern;
•
For personalization
of your experiences with us, including to remember your interests and preferences, customize the contests, allow you to connect with other users or invite others to join Vivid Picks based on the contact information you agree to provide us, listings and services we share with you on the Site, Apps and through email, track and categorize your activity and interests on our Site and Apps (including by identifying the different devices you use), and make your gaming and/or shopping experience with us more relevant;
• For marketing and advertising
, to send you marketing and advertising communications based on your interactions with us, including through the Site, Apps and email, to segment and build audiences and engage in interest-based advertising (referred to under certain laws as “targeted advertising”), to provide social media features, and to measure and analyze the performance of our advertising and online content;
• For analytics
, to understand how you use our Site and Apps, analyze our Site and Apps traffic, measure and analyze the performance of our ads on third party platforms, evaluate the efficacy of our affiliate partnerships, understand the impact of our advertising and online content, to gather demographic information about our individual users and aggregate user base, to determine the methods and devices used to access our Site and Apps, and to improve our services;
• For our business purposes
, to operate and improve upon our business and lawful business activities, to identify new customers, to update, expand, and analyze our records, for research, to determine your satisfaction with our Site, Apps and services, to detect and prevent wireless device or other fraud or misuse of our services, to enforce, apply or comply with any of our terms or policies, including but not limited to this Policy, and for any other business purpose that is permitted bylaw; and
• For legal, contractual and safety purposes
, including to defend or protect us, our customers, you, or third parties from harm or in legal proceedings, protect our rights, protect our security and the security of our customers, employees, and property, respond to court orders, lawsuits, subpoenas, and government requests, address legal and regulatory compliance, comply with contracts and other agreements to which we are a party, and notify you of changes to our terms, policies, or practices.
4. How Do We Share Personal Information?
Except as provided in this Policy, we will not disclose, sell, or rent your personal information to any third parties without your consent.
We may share personal information as described below:
• With service providers that perform certain functions
. These third parties may only use personal information as necessary to provide these services to us and not for their own promotional purposes. These include the following service providers who use personal information:
For the purpose of verifying your identity and conducting anti-fraud checks.
For the purpose of preventing fraudulent ticket purchases and sales through our marketplace and fraudulent or unauthorized contest play on our Apps.
For the purpose of analyzing data to provide you a better customer experience.
For the purpose of gathering feedback on your experience with Vivid Picks.
For the purpose of providing you with customer support. This may include offshore customer contact and call centers.
For the purpose of delivering your tickets, whether that is electronically or physically, and ensuring you successfully access your seats.
• With select business partners
, so that they can provide you with special offers, promotional materials, and other materials that may be of interest to you. This includes our affiliate partners and other partners that are listed on our Site and Apps. The information we give these partners may include your name, email address, phone number, and billing address.  These entities’ use of such information is subject to their respective privacy policies.
• With marketing and advertising partners
, we may allow marketing and advertising partners to use cookies, pixel tags, web beacons, SDKs,  scripts and/or similar technologies on our Site, Apps and emails to collect information about you and your activities on the Site and Apps, as described further in Section 8 below. We also share information directly with marketing and advertising partners to help segment and build audiences to support our interest-based advertising on third-party platforms. We do not use cookies or similar technologies for the purpose of delivering retargeted ads on third party websites or services.
• To respond to subpoenas
, lawful requests by public authorities, court orders, or other legal process, as required by law or regulations, to establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims, or to report violations of the Vivid Picks eligibility requirements to third parties, including employers of individuals affiliated with other daily fantasy sites;
• To protect us and our users, with the rights
, property, or safety of Vivid Picks, our users, or others, including for fraud protection;
• In the event of a sale or merger
, of some or all of our business or a merger with another company, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our Site and/or Apps of any change in ownership; or
• With your prior consent to do so.
We also may share personal information that you have provided to us about others with certain third parties that require it such as sports teams, leagues, ticketing partners, and event sponsors or organizers, for example, to grant passes to your guests, or with our affiliate partners, for example, to fulfill the terms of any welcome offer or other Vivid Picks offer you accepted by creating a Vivid Picks account using the affiliate’s unique code. These recipients may also use the personal information for their marketing purposes.
5. Third Party Sites and Frames
Our Site and Apps include links to other websites whose privacy practices may differ from those of Vivid Picks. If you submit personal information to any of those sites, or to any third parties, your information is governed by their privacy policies. In addition, some of our pages utilize framing techniques to serve content from our partners while preserving the look and feel of our Site and Apps. When we use framing techniques, we display the logo of our partner, so that you will know that you are engaging with a third party.  Please be aware that you are providing your personal information to these third parties and not to www.vividpicks.com, and the third parties’ privacy policy will govern their use of your information. We encourage you to carefully read the privacy policy of any other website you visit, and of any third parties to whom you provide personal information.
6. Security and Retention
We use Secure Socket Layers (“SSL”) encryption technology through third-party providers where your personal and account information is required (such as a credit card number).  All transaction information is processed under encrypted channels.
We follow generally accepted industry standards to protect your personal information, both during transmission and once we receive it. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100%secure, however. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
We will keep your personal information only for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, to provide you with products or services, to carry out legitimate business interests, and where otherwise required or permitted by law. If you have any questions about security on our Site and Apps, you can email us at
privacy@vividpicks.com
.
